cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about image super-resolution using a deep convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel residual dense network architecture, which involves the use of dense connected convolutional layers and a contiguous memory mechanism. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all related to deep learning and neural networks. Finally, since the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
